text: Example 5.1. Suppose our list contains n integers between 000 and 999 inclu- sive. Let’s use base b = 10 so then we need d = 3 of them. If we use Radix- Sort+CountingSort then the underlying CountingSort has £ = max = 9 and therefore is ©(n +9) and so the resulting RadixSort will be ©(3(n+9)) = ©(n).
